The '''2010 [[Melbourne Football Club]]''' season was the club's 111th year in the [[VFL/AFL]] since it began in 1897.
Melbourne played 14 games at the [[MCG]], 10 of which were home games. They also played a home match at [[TIO Stadium]] in [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]] against [[Port Adelaide Power|Port Adelaide]] in Round 9.<ref>{{cite web|last=Burgan|first=Matt|title='Old-fashioned' draw pleases Dees|url=http://www.melbournefc.com.au/news/newsarticle/tabid/7415/newsid/86539/default.aspx|publisher=Melbourne FC|accessdate=1 September 2010}}</ref> It was [[Dean Bailey]]'s third year as senior coach. [[James McDonald (footballer)|James McDonald]] continued as the club's captain until retiring at the end of the year.
In August, Melbourne announced it was officially debt free.<ref>{{Cite news| last=Niall| first=Jake| title= Demons wipe out last of their $5m debt| publisher=The Age| date=5/8/10| url=http://www.theage.com.au/afl/afl-news/demons-wipe-out-last-of-their-5m-debt-20100805-11fu2.html| accessdate=5 August 2010}}</ref> The same night Melbourne also unveiled its new logo.<ref>{{Cite news| title=Debt-free Demons unveil striking new logo| publisher=Australian Football League (AFL)| date=5/8/10| url=http://www.afl.com.au/tabid/208/default.aspx?newsid=99704| accessdate=8 August 2010}}</ref>
