== China Tour == [[Melbourne Football Club|Melbourne]] competed in the [[Kaspersky]] Cup Exhibition Match against the [[Brisbane Lions]] on 17 October in [[Shanghai]], [[China]] winning by 5 points. [[Liam Jurrah]] kicked 5 goals in front of an estimated 5,000 crowd.<ref>{{cite web|last=Burgan|first=Matt|title=Dees win Shanghai thriller|url=http://www.melbournefc.com.au/news/newsarticle/tabid/7415/newsid/104212/default.aspx|publisher=MFC|accessdate=17 October 2010}}</ref> Scores: '''Melbourne: 12.12.84''' Brisbane: 11.13.79
==Awards==
Melbourne's annual Best and Fairest night was held on 2 September, at [[Crown Casino]]. [[Brad Green (footballer)|Brad Green]] capped off an excellent year, winning his first [[Keith 'Bluey' Truscott Medal|Keith 'Bluey' Truscott Trophy]], finishing 18 votes ahead of defender [[James Frawley (Australian rules footballer)|James Frawley]], and also winning the Ron Barassi Leadership Award and the Leading Goalkicker Award.<ref>{{cite web|last=Holmesby|first=Luke|title=Green wins his first Melbourne best and fairest|url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/newsarticle/tabid/208/newsid/101798/default.aspx|publisher=AFL|accessdate=5 September 2010}}</ref>
